title: Sports Minute: Here is the latest Kentucky sports from The AP
text:
Sports Minute: Here is the latest Kentucky sports from The AP - WDRB 41 Louisville News Member Center: Sports Minute: Here is the latest Kentucky sports from The AP Posted: Updated: 
BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) - Western Kentucky's high-powered offense dominated from the outset as the Hilltoppers scored on eight of 10 first-half possessions, routing Middle Tennessee, 58-28, on Saturday in Conference USA play. Quarterback Brandon Doughty led Western Kentucky, throwing five TD passes in the first half alone for 52 points before the break. 
MURRAY, Ky. (AP) - KD Humphries and Roman Clay both ran for a pair of touchdowns - all in the first half - and Murray State ran away from Austin Peay 34-18 on Saturday. Humphries was 32 of 51 for 286 yards and Clay had 118 yards as Murray State (2-4, 1-2 Ohio Valley) ran up a 31-6 halftime lead. 
MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) - Austin Gahafer threw for 363 yards and three touchdowns as Morehead State rallied past Butler 34-21 in Pioneer League play on Saturday. Gahafer has accounted for 20 of 21 touchdowns this season for Morehead State (3-3, 2-1), and has thrown for at least three TDS in five straight games. 
DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) - Thomas Sykes intercepted Dalton Oliver in overtime, preserving a 14-7 win for Davidson over Kentucky Wesleyan on Saturday. Davidson got the ball first in overtime, and Taylor Mitchell found William Morris for a 9-yard score to give the Wildcats their second lead of the game. Needing a touchdown, Kentucky Wesleyan went for it on fourth-and-2 from the 17, and Sykes intercepted Oliver's attempt, ensuring Davidson's first win of the season.
